28 ciò avvenia di duol sanza martìri, 29 ch’avean le turbe, ch’eran molte e grandi, 30 d’infanti e di femmine e di viri.

query.result:
31 The good master to me: “You do not ask 32 who are these spirits that you see? 33 Now I want you to know, before you go further,
34 that they did not sin; and if they have merits, 35 it is not enough, because they did not have baptism, 36 which is the gate of the faith that you believe;
37 and if they were before Christianity, 38 they did not worship properly to God: 39 and of these such am I myself.”

55 He drew with him the shadow of the first parent, 56 of Abel his son and that of Noah, 57 of Moses the lawgiver and obedient one;
58 Abraham patriarch and David king, 59 Israel with his father and with his sons 60 and with Rachel, for whom he had so much faith,
61 and many others, and he made them blessed.

79 Meanwhile a voice was heard by me:
80 “Honor the most high poet;
81 his shadow returns, which had departed.”

85 The good master began to say:
86 “Look at the one with the sword in hand,
87 who comes before the three as a lord:

88 that one is Homer, supreme poet;
89 the other is Horace, satirist who comes;
90 Ovid is the third, and the last Lucan.”

