query.result:
133 All look at him, all render him honor: 134 there I saw Socrates and Plato, 135 who stand closer to the others;
136 Democritus who places the world by chance, 137 Diogenes, Anaxagoras and Thales, 138 Empedocles, Heraclitus and Zeno;
139 and I saw the good receiver of whom, 140 I say Dioscorides; and I saw Orpheus, 141 Tully and Linus and Seneca moral;
142 Euclid the geometer and Ptolemy, 143 Hippocrates, Avicenna and Galen, 144 Averroes, who made the great commentary.
